  "prompt": "What are some of the most common examples of an imperative sentence?",
  "response": "An imperative sentence typically gives a command, makes a request, or offers an invitation. Here are some common examples:\n\n1. **Commands:**\n   - Close the door.\n   - Turn off the lights.\n   - Stop talking.\n\n2. **Requests:**\n   - Please pass the salt.\n   - Can you help me with this?\n   - Bring me the book.\n\n3. **Invitations:**\n   - Come to my party.\n   - Join us for dinner.\n   - Visit us this weekend.\n\nImperative sentences often imply a sense of urgency or immediate action and usually end with a period, though they can also end with an exclamation mark for emphasis.",
